This paper deals with the problem of compressing a weighted graph and building a sketch that can approximate certain values of the Laplacian matrix. This involves techniques from data structures, spectral graph theory, and numerical linear algebra. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
